A corporal in the Republic of Korea Marine Corps goes on a killing spree while on duty at a guard post on South Korea's Ganghwa Island, killing 3 people and injuring 2 others. (Yonhap News) (BBC)Canadian Freedom Waves to Gaza organizers say activists on the Canadian ship Tahrir that, along with the Irish MV Saoirse, who were headed to the Gaza Strip, were intercepted by Israeli troops. The activists refused to voluntarily leave the ship; Israel says no one was hurt.(The Globe and Mail) (CBC) (Salem-News.com) (Jerusalem Post) (Ynetnews.com)